<sec>
<st>
History</st>
<p>

eCos was initially developed by <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.8">
<institution wordnetid="108053576" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../310/43310.xml">
Cygnus Solutions</link></institution>
</company>
 which was later bought by <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../386/26386.xml">
Red Hat</link></company>
. In early 2002, Red Hat ceased development of eCos and laid off the staff that were working on the project<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref> who then formed their own company, <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../470/2676470.xml">
eCosCentric</link>, in order to continue development and provide commercial support for eCos. In January 2004, at the request of the eCos developers, Red Hat agreed to transfer its eCos copyrights to the <group wordnetid="100031264" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../437/18949437.xml">
Free Software Foundation</link></group>
<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%223%22])">3</ref>. The transfer was finally executed in October 2005.</p>

